title: Grateful Dead Live at Field House, Rensselaer Polytechnic Institute on 1978-05-07
description: Jack Straw, Dire Wolf, Finiculi Finicula, Mexicali Blues-> Mama Tried, Tennessee Jed, It's All Over Now, Friend Of The Devil, Passenger, Brown Eyed Women, The Music Never Stopped Scarlet Begonias-> Fire On The Mountain, Estimated Prophet-> He's Gone-> Drums-> Iko Iko-> The Other One-> Black Peter-> Around & Around, E: U.S. Blues

reviews.review_text: Gym Floor Upon further review, the band seems a bit "off" this night. But, hey, that's one of the things I liked about them.
yup, bit off, esp in s2 First set is quite good. Second set becomes a bit monolithic and draggy.

A bit "off", are you crazy? This is one of my favorite shows. The entire thing is smoking from start to finish.

Starts with a strong jack straw. Next is dire wolf. By far one of the best dire wolf ever. The Jed and Music never stopped are also stand out versions. 

Seconds set starts smoking right away with scarlet/fire, really good fire. One of my favorites.
Estimated/Hes Gone very good as well. Black peter is where this show goes from great to amazing. This is the best Black Peter ever, so much emotion and soul is poured into the mid solo and outro. Simply amazing.

Far from off My oh my this another smokin show from Barry "not going to atempt spelling the last name cause to lazy to look back and get it correct" Holy shit he knows the best spot night in night out

FIRST TIME This was my first Dead show and went on to see them ~40 times.  I will never forget the energy that this show had.  First set rocks, while the 2nd set meanders through the wonderful energy of Scarlet/Fire and The other One.  I will never forget this experience in a hockey arena that was general admission.  So cool to hear a great recording of a great show that was the beginning of a long strange trip!
